description: primesieve is a command-line program that generates primes using a highly optimized sieve of Eratosthenes implementation. It counts the primes below 10^10 in just 0.45 seconds on an Intel Core i7-6700 CPU (4 x 3.4GHz). primesieve can generate primes and prime k-tuplets up to 2^64.
author: Kim Walisch
